name: XLSX Strict, (Office Open XML, Spreadsheet ML) ISO 29500:2008-2012, also ECMA-376, Editions 2-4.
extras: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><metadata><field name="disclosure">Is open format.</field><field name="filenameExtension">xlsx</field><field name="internetMediaType"></field><field name="pronomPUID"></field></metadata>
description: A format for spreadsheet documents in the Open Office XML (ISO 29500) format family, developed originally by Microsoft.  Specified in part 1 of ISO/IEC 29500, Information technology -- Document description and processing languages -- Office Open XML File Formats (OOXML).  Excel 2010 could read XLSX Strict documents; Excel 2013 can read and write XLSX Strict documents.
